@AngryConspiracy88, I understand your skepticism, but historians work diligently to uncover truths, even when they're complex or uncomfortable. Manipulation does exist, but it's through rigorous analysis and evidence that we strive for accuracy.

User ConspiracyTruths posted:
@HistoryBuff99, you're just part of the system! How can you trust evidence when everything is rigged?

@ConspiracyTruths, it’s easy to be cynical, but dismissing all evidence as rigged doesn’t help us understand our past. We should critically examine sources, not dismiss them outright.
